#: ../../source/api/prepshot._model.unit_commitment.rst:2
msgid "unit_commitment"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:1
msgid "Unit-commitment (UC) overlay -- clustered MILP formulation."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:3
msgid ""
"Standard \"clustered UC\" representation, used by GenX, PowNet, and "
"similar planning models that need the MILP fidelity without modelling "
"each plant individually:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:7
msgid ""
"Each UC-eligible tech (typically thermal: coal, gas, oil) is a cluster of"
" identical units of size ``tech_unit_size[te]`` MW. The total cluster "
"capacity is ``cap_existing[y, z, te]``, so the *integer* number of units "
"is ``cap / unit_size``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:12
msgid "New decision variables per ``(h, m, y, z, te)``:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:14
msgid "``online[h]`` -- number of units online (integer, 0..N_units)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:15
msgid "``startup[h]`` -- number of units started this hour (integer >=0)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:16
msgid "``shutdown[h]`` -- number of units shut down this hour (integer >=0)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:19
msgid "New constraints:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:21
msgid ""
"**State evolution** (h > hour[0]): ``online[h] - online[h-1] = startup[h]"
" - shutdown[h]``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:23
msgid ""
"**Capacity bound on dispatch**: ``gen[h] <= online[h] * unit_size * "
"p_max_pu * dt`` ``gen[h] >= online[h] * unit_size * p_min_pu * dt``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:27
msgid ""
"These REPLACE the standard ``gen <= cap_existing * p_max_pu * dt`` bound "
"for UC-eligible techs (the standard one is now redundant because ``online"
" <= N_units = cap/unit_size``)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:30
msgid ""
"**Minimum up time** (``online >= sum of recent startups``): ``online[h] "
">= sum_{i=0..MinUp-1} startup[h-i]``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:32
msgid ""
"**Minimum down time** (``offline >= sum of recent shutdowns``): "
"``(N_units - online[h]) >= sum_{i=0..MinDown-1} shutdown[h-i]``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:35
msgid "New cost terms (added to the objective):"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:37
msgid "``startup_cost[te] * unit_size[te] * startup[h]`` per hour"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:38
msgid "``no_load_cost[te] * unit_size[te] * online[h] * dt`` per hour"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:40
msgid ""
"Both NPV-discounted via ``var_factor[y, z]`` like the rest of the "
"variable cost."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:43
msgid ""
"This module turns PREP-SHOT into a **MILP** when enabled. HiGHS solves "
"it; runtime grows several-fold relative to the LP. Recommended only for "
"small-to-medium scenarios -- ``three_zone`` (48 hours) takes a few "
"seconds; full-year 8760-hour PCM mode with UC is feasible only in "
"rolling-horizon windows (see ``prepshot.pcm``)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:50
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:52
msgid "Add to ``config.json``::"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:59
msgid ""
"When ``is_uc`` is missing or ``false``, the module is a no-op and PREP-"
"SHOT stays LP. When ``uc_relaxation`` is ``\"continuous\"``, the binaries"
" become continuous in their natural ranges -- useful for scaling tests "
"and for warm-starting an integer solve."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:65
msgid "Inputs"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:67
msgid "All optional (rows missing or files missing -> safe defaults):"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:69
msgid "``tech_uc_eligible.csv`` -- ``tech, eligible``. Default ``0``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:70
msgid ""
"``tech_unit_size.csv`` -- ``tech, value`` (MW). Default ``1`` (one "
"cluster = one unit at full cap, equivalent to LP behaviour)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:72
msgid "``tech_min_up_time.csv`` -- ``tech, value`` (hours). Default ``1``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:73
msgid "``tech_min_down_time.csv`` -- ``tech, value`` (hours). Default ``1``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:74
msgid "``tech_startup_cost.csv`` -- ``tech, value`` ($/MW). Default ``0``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment:75
msgid "``tech_no_load_cost.csv`` -- ``tech, value`` ($/MW-h). Default ``0``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints:1
msgid "Bases: :py:class:`object`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints:1
msgid "Clustered unit-commitment constraints + cost terms."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: of
#: prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints.gen_low_uc_rule:1
msgid "``gen[h] >= online[h] * unit_size * p_min_pu * dt``."
msgstr ""

#: of
#: prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints.gen_up_uc_rule:1
msgid "``gen[h] <= online[h] * unit_size * p_max_pu * dt``."
msgstr ""

#: of
#: prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints.min_down_rule:1
msgid "``(N_units - online[h]) >= sum_{i=0..MinDown-1} shutdown[h-i]``."
msgstr ""

#: of
#: prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints.min_up_rule:1
msgid ""
"``online[h] >= sum_{i=0..MinUp-1} startup[h-i]`` -- if a unit started in "
"any of the last MinUp hours, it must be online now."
msgstr ""

#: of
#: prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints.n_unit_bound_rule:1
msgid ""
"``online[h] <= N_units`` and force online=startup=shutdown=0 for non-"
"eligible (z, te) cells."
msgstr ""

#: of
#: prepshot._model.unit_commitment.AddUnitCommitmentConstraints.state_evolution_rule:1
msgid ""
"``online[h] - online[h-1] = startup[h] - shutdown[h]`` for every hour "
"after the first in the modelled set. The first hour's online state is "
"free (initialised by the LP optimum)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment.add_uc_cost_terms:1
msgid ""
"Return the UC cost contribution (startup + no-load) as an ExprBuilder, "
"NPV-discounted by ``var_factor`` and divided by ``weight`` to align with "
"the rest of ``cost_var``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.unit_commitment.add_uc_cost_terms:5
msgid ""
"Returns a zero ExprBuilder when UC is disabled, so callers can add it "
"unconditionally."
msgstr ""

